  -- re-keys over THIS list, so the wire and the committed registry coincide).
  -- THE FLAG-DAY: emit the DEPLOYED WELDED cohort (`v3RegistryCapOpenDep` вЂ” the 36 cohort members
  -- carry the capacity-floor refuse; the cap-open tail is identical). The apex's `Rfix` re-keys over
  -- the SAME list (via `v3RegistryHeap = v3RegistryCapOpenDep ++ вЂ¦`), so the committed VK bytes and
  -- the soundness apex coincide on the refuse вЂ” the flip is REAL, not staged.
  -- THE AVAILABILITY FLIP: override the two flipped cohort keys with the hardened wire members
  -- (the availability weld gates + 15-bit range teeth + the SAME refuse/rc wrappers). Every other
  -- member emits its committed bare bytes unchanged.
  -- The cap-open transfer key rides the SAME flip: the LIVE `transferCapOpenEffVmDescriptor2R24`
  -- routes the hardened cap-open member (the appendix re-hosted on the borrow-weld base вЂ” same
  -- wrap class, cap-authorized route; RotatedKernelRefinementCapOpenAvail).
  -- The FEE'D transfer key (tail position 44, the live sovereign transfer's effect-vm leg) rides
  -- the flip too: `transferFeeV3AvailWire` вЂ” the В§11.8 fee availability weld (MID-linked
  -- borrow/carry chains closing the wrap through BOTH debit legs, amount AND fee) under the same
  -- fee pin + rc wrapper; discharge in RotatedKernelRefinementFeeAvail.
